c9cbba54-5bea-46a3-aa37-15f73685533b.Value:
name: Table_Template                     		#required
description: My template description            #optional

physicalName: ${objectPhysicalName}      	    #default: '${objectPhysicalName}'


# The following variables can also be used in template values
#
# ${objectPhysicalName}  -  the default name for a new table in a given project, respecting naming conventions
# ${parentPhysicalName}  -  the physical name when creating the template from a parent object, otherwise blank
# ${parentLogicalName}   -  the logical name when creating the template from a parent object, otherwise blank
# ${parentSchema}        -  the schema when creating the template from a parent object, otherwise blank
#
# For the full YAML template documentation, please see our Help Center:
# https://intercom.help/SqlDBMhelpcenter/en/articles/8662960-table-templates

8da42f07-6182-4612-8261-cbfe85dc7223.Value:
name: satellite (default)_Clone
physicalName: sat_${parentPhysicalName}
color: yellow
inheritIdentifiersAs: none
inheritAttributes: true
generateRelationship: none
primaryColumns:
  - name: md5_hub_${parentPhysicalName}
    dataType: binary
    nullable: false
  - name: load_dts
    dataType: timestamp_ntz(9)
    nullable: false
defaultColumns:
  - name: hash_diff
    dataType: binary
    position: last
  - name: rec_src
    dataType: varchar(16777216)
    position: last

external.Name: external
external.Template:
location: <string>
file_format: <string>
row_format: <string>
tbl_properties: <string>      
partitions: 
  - name: <string>
    data_type: <string>
    description: <string>
    meta: <dictionary>
  - ...
<additional_property>: <additional_value>

freshness.Name: freshness
freshness.Template:
warn_after:
  count:  <positive_integer>
  period:  minute | hour | day
error_after:
  count:  <positive_integer>
  period: minute | hour | day
filter: <where-condition>

model_config.Name: model_config
model_config.Template:
enabled: true | false
tags: <string> | [<string>]
pre-hook: <sql-statement> | [<sql-statement>]
post-hook: <sql-statement> | [<sql-statement>]
database: <string>
alias: <string>
persist_docs: <string>
full_refresh: <string>
meta: {<dictionary>}
grants: {<dictionary>}
contract: {<dictionary>}

quoting.Name: quoting
quoting.Template:
database: true | false
schema: true | false
identifier: true | false

database: #<database_name>
schema: #<schema_name>
loader: #<string>

# requires v1.1+
config:

freshness:
  warn_after:
    count: #<positive_integer>

quoting:

  schema: #true | false
  identifier: #true | false
